# Gamma Presentation Integration Rules

## Iframe Integration Standards
Follow the established pattern from course pages like [nd2025/nd01/index.html](mdc:nd2025/nd01/index.html):

### Iframe Configuration
```html
<iframe src="https://gamma.app/embed/[PRESENTATION_ID]" 
        allow="fullscreen" 
        title="[Descriptive Title]"
        onload="hideLoading()"
        loading="lazy"
        sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-presentation">
</iframe>
```

### Loading State Management
- Always include a loading spinner with descriptive text
- Use fade-in transition when iframe loads
- Implement proper error handling for failed loads

### Presentation ID Management
- Store Gamma presentation IDs in a consistent location
- Use descriptive titles that match the course structure
- Ensure presentation IDs are current and accessible

### Responsive Considerations
- Use `100vh` and `100dvh` for proper mobile viewport handling
- Implement proper scaling for different screen sizes
- Test on various devices and browsers

### Security and Performance
- Use appropriate sandbox attributes for security
- Implement lazy loading for better performance
- Include proper error handling and fallbacks

### JavaScript Integration
```javascript
function hideLoading() {
  const loading = document.getElementById('loading');
  const iframe = document.querySelector('iframe');
  
  loading.style.display = 'none';
  iframe.classList.add('loaded');
}
```

## Best Practices
- Test presentations on multiple devices before deployment
- Ensure presentations are accessible and properly embedded
- Maintain consistent loading experience across all course pages
- Use descriptive titles for better accessibility